14. Methods of text indexing
- There are two primary methods of text indexing, namely:-
a. Keyword Indexing
- This is the most common form of text indexing on the web.
- In this method, text are indexed by use of key word or in some case, by phrases
- Unless the author specifies the key-word for the document, it's up to the search engine to determined them by pulling out words that it believes to be of significance e.g. words at the top of the document or those that are repeated more often in throughout the document
- Key word searches find it difficult to distinguish between words that are spelled the same way but mean different things /OR/ words spelled differently but mean the same thing; therefore may results in hits that are completely irrelevant to the query
- It cannot return hits on key-words that mean the same thing but are not actually entered in your query e.g. a query on heart diseases would not return a document that use the word "cardiac" instead of "heart"
b. Concept-base Indexing
- It tries to determine what you mean(unlike key-word indexing), not just what you say
- They do this by checking documents for the dominant theme or concept, which are then indexed.
- They return hits on documents that are about the subject/theme you are exploring, even if the words in the document do not precisely match the word you entered into the query
- Some concept base indexing rely on sophisticated linguistics and artificial intelligence theory e.g. by calculating the frequency with which certain important words appears. The search engine concludes, by statistical analysis, that the pieces are "about" a certain subjects e.g. the word "heart", when used in the medical/health context, would be likely to appear with words such as coronary, artery, lung, stroke, cholesterol, blood, arteriosclerosis etc. if the same word "hearth" appears in a document with other words such as flower, candy, love, passion, valentine etc., a very different context is established and the search engine returns hits on the subject of romance
