\section*{3. Various threats to data security.}

\section*{i. Physical damage and theft}
i. Theft
- In an event of computer theft, one will lose data and information stored in it plus computer itself
- In most of the cases, data stored in the computer is by far more expensive that the computer itself.
ii. System crash

This is the total computer failure that occurs when the computer is damaged.
iii. Protection against theft and system crash

One should regularly backup his/her data so that you can restore the information to the point of last back up. Incomplete backup (infrequent, incomplete), may lead to
a. Loss of data stored in the system
b. In the case of computer theft, one will loss the hardware itself

\section*{ii. Viruses}
i. Definition
- This is a hidden self-replicating computer program/software written with ill motives by mischievous individuals with bad intention and spread to other computers by sharing infected files or/and programs
- Viruses are designed to "self replicate" or "clone" themselves, that is, secretly copy themselves from place to place. This process is called infection
ii. Virus detection - we detect a virus when we experience one or more of the following symptoms
- Slow down of computer programs or slow down of the computer general performance
- Unusual and frequent error messages
- Change in file size or replication of computer files
- Loss or modification of data
- System failure

\section*{iii. Protection against viruses}
- Installing Anti-virus software in your computer
- Files should be backup so that it can be restored back in the event of a system failure
- One should avoid using programs of unknown origins
- One should not open an attached file from unknown origin in an email
- Always check for viruses on portable disks when using it to transfer files from one computer to another

\section*{iii. Software Bugs}
* These are errors in computer software that are usually unintentional.
- Running a computer with a bug can lead to serious malfunctioning to the computer and may lead to loss of data

\section*{iv. Trojan horses}
* These are dangerous pieces of computer program that comes intentionally hidden or appears like a software that is well-behave and useful

